In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 6 through May 12, 2012, as National Charter Schools Week. The President emphasizes the importance of providing children with a world-class education and recognizes the role of charter schools in strengthening American education. Charter schools, whether created by parents and teachers or community leaders, serve as incubators of innovation in education. They have the flexibility to develop new teaching models and methods to meet students' needs while maintaining strong accountability and high standards. The President highlights that a good education is now essential in an economy where knowledge is valuable. He calls for a commitment to ensuring all children receive a high-quality education that expands their horizons and inspires them to develop their talents. President Obama commends charter schools, teachers, and administrators and encourages states and communities to support charter schools and the students they serve.